\r\n\r\nFor the moment (without this PR) you can do by default:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\n\r\n\tvar clock = new THREE.Clock();\r\n\tclock.start();\r\n\r\n\tself.performance.next(123);\r\n\tassert.ok( clock.getElapsedTime() === 0.123 , \"okay\");\r\n\r\n\tself.performance.next(100);\r\n\tassert.ok( clock.getElapsedTime() === 0.223 , \"okay\");\r\n\r\n\tclock.stop();\r\n\r\n\tself.performance.next(1000);\r\n\r\n        \/\/ This assert is FALSE ! You can't stop the Clock\r\n\tassert.ok( clock.getElapsedTime() === 0.223 , \"don't update time if the clock was stopped\");\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhy ? Because in `getDelat` that is call by `getElapsedTime` you have:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\n\r\ngetDelta: function () {\r\n\r\n\tvar diff = 0;\r\n\r\n\tif ( this.autoStart && ! this.running ) {\r\n\r\n\t\tthis.start();\r\n\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\tif ( this.running ) {\r\n\r\n\t\tvar newTime = ( performance || Date ).now();\r\n\r\n\t\tdiff = ( newTime - this.oldTime ) \/ 1000;\r\n\t\tthis.oldTime = newTime;\r\n\r\n\t\tthis.elapsedTime += diff;\r\n\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\treturn diff;\r\n\r\n}\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nand `autostart` is true by default (that is bad) and you can't set it to false by default due to backward compat...\r\n\r\nThe goal of this PR is to allow to stop the clock without breaking backward compatibility by default !\r\n\r\n\r\nIn regards to unstopable mode, i keep the \"feature\" in case it was wanted but i'm really not sure it was !\r\n","created_at":"2017-01-28T21:29:44.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/10656#issuecomment-275875954","id":275875954,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/10656","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI3NTg3NTk1NA==","updated_at":"2017-01-28T21:29:44.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/275875954","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Itee\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Itee\/events{\/privacy}